1. Data is given in csv format, don't change it to xlsx directly.
2. Open new xlsx file and import csv file using power query
3. Map chart option is not available for versions prior 2016, so don't worry if you couldn't find it
4. Map chart is only available for normal tables, so copy the data from pivot table and make
separate table to make map chart
5. Make different pivot tables in different sheets as included in snaps
6. Don't put different pivot tables in the same sheet. And follow a good naming convention
otherwise things will easily get clumpsy.
7. After making all pivot tables and charts in different tables, then cut and paste the pivot charts
to the dashboard from their respective sheets
8. Slicers should be connected to all concerned pivot charts accordingly
